WEBVTT

00:00.913 --> 00:05.440
[UPBEAT MUSIC]

00:05.570 --> 00:09.009
[HEAVY VEHICLES RUNNING]
[TRUCK HORN]

00:26.069 --> 00:28.767
-[CHUCKLES] LISTEN
TO MY HOROSCOPE.

00:28.898 --> 00:30.508
"TODAY IS YOUR DAY.

00:30.639 --> 00:33.076
"EXCITEMENT AND
ROMANCE RUN WILD.

00:33.207 --> 00:35.513
"YOUR LIFE IS ON FIRE."

00:35.644 --> 00:37.907
THAT IS SO NOT MY DAY.

00:38.038 --> 00:41.432
THE MOST EXCITING THING I'VE
DONE IS PICKED UP LITTER.

00:41.998 --> 00:43.478
OH, AND MY DATE LAST NIGHT?

00:43.608 --> 00:44.740
STOOD ME UP.

00:44.870 --> 00:46.307
-WHAT'S MINE SAY?

00:46.437 --> 00:47.917
-UH, WHEN'S YOUR
BIRTHDAY AGAIN?

00:48.048 --> 00:49.136
-AH, THAT'S VERY FUNNY.

00:49.266 --> 00:51.355
-UH, LET'S SEE.

00:51.486 --> 00:53.531
"A DAY TO BE EXTRA CAREFUL.

00:53.662 --> 00:56.578
"WHAT SEEMS HARMLESS
CAN BE VERY DANGEROUS.

00:56.708 --> 00:59.320
"PISCES FIGURES PROMINENTLY."

00:59.450 --> 01:00.756
PUT THE TRASH IN THERE.
-JESSIE: HEY.

01:00.886 --> 01:02.236
-HEY.

01:02.366 --> 01:03.541
-PEOPLE ARE COMPLAINING
ABOUT A TERRIBLE SMELL

01:03.672 --> 01:04.890
THAT'S COMING OUT
OF THAT TUNNEL.

01:05.021 --> 01:06.544
-NO PROBLEM,
WE'LL CHECK IT OUT.

01:06.675 --> 01:07.632
BACK TO YOUR TOWER, HUH.

01:07.763 --> 01:08.416
-ALL RIGHT.
-SEE YA.

01:08.546 --> 01:09.678
-THANKS.

01:09.808 --> 01:12.681
[BEACH CROWD CHATTER]

01:14.726 --> 01:17.251
[CONSTRUCTION MACHINERY RUNNING]

01:20.080 --> 01:21.472
[CONSTRUCTION CREW CHATTER]

01:21.603 --> 01:23.213
-INCH AND A HALF EACH.

01:23.344 --> 01:24.693
-UCH.

01:25.433 --> 01:26.738
UCH.

01:26.869 --> 01:28.000
WHEW!

01:28.914 --> 01:30.525
-SMELLS LIKE SOMETHING
DIED IN THERE.

01:30.655 --> 01:31.569
-SEA LION?

01:32.266 --> 01:33.963
-I DON'T KNOW,
LET'S CHECK IT OUT.

01:34.920 --> 01:36.661
-MAYBE WE SHOULD CALL
ANIMAL CONTROL FIRST.

01:36.792 --> 01:39.011
-NO, NO, NO, LET'S SEE
WHAT WE'RE DEALING WITH.

01:39.142 --> 01:40.491
-YEAH.

01:54.505 --> 01:55.289
LISTEN.

01:56.028 --> 01:57.073
WHAT IS THAT?

01:57.769 --> 02:00.772
-[SNIFFS] GAS LEAK.

02:00.903 --> 02:03.514
THE CONSTRUCTION CREW MUST
HAVE SEVERED A GAS LINE.

02:08.780 --> 02:09.824
-DAD.

02:11.000 --> 02:12.567
-COME ON!

02:30.976 --> 02:33.153
-WHAT'D YOUR HOROSCOPE SAY?

02:34.110 --> 02:37.113
-MY LIFE IS ON FIRE.

02:38.419 --> 02:39.811
-THAT'S WHAT I THOUGHT.

02:47.863 --> 02:51.388
♪ SOME PEOPLE STAND
IN THE DARKNESS ♪

02:51.519 --> 02:55.305
♪ AFRAID TO STEP
INTO THE LIGHT ♪

02:56.001 --> 02:59.309
♪ SOME PEOPLE NEED
TO HELP SOMEBODY ♪

02:59.440 --> 03:03.008
♪ WHEN THE EDGE OF
SURRENDER'S IN SIGHT ♪

03:03.139 --> 03:05.663
♪ DON'T YOU WORRY

03:05.794 --> 03:08.927
♪ IT'S GONNA BE ALRIGHT

03:11.756 --> 03:13.584
♪ CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

03:13.715 --> 03:17.980
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT. ♪

03:20.243 --> 03:22.680
♪ I'LL BE READY

03:22.811 --> 03:24.595
♪ I'LL BE READY

03:24.726 --> 03:26.118
♪ NEVER YOU FEAR

03:26.249 --> 03:28.251
♪ NO DON'T YOU FEAR

03:28.382 --> 03:31.211
♪ I'LL BE READY

03:31.341 --> 03:34.823
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

03:34.953 --> 03:37.652
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE.

03:52.841 --> 03:54.843
[WATER LAPPING]
[SEAGULL CALLING]

03:58.455 --> 04:01.066
[FUNKY MUSIC]

04:02.546 --> 04:03.678
-YO, RANDY, WHAT
TOOK YOU SO LONG?

04:03.808 --> 04:04.635
-YEAH?

04:04.766 --> 04:05.767
-JOSIE.

04:05.897 --> 04:07.464
-YEAH.
-COME ON, LET'S DANCE.

04:07.595 --> 04:09.161
DANCE WITH ME, COME ON.

04:09.292 --> 04:10.162
I'M COMING OUT.

04:12.426 --> 04:14.732
COME ON, IT'S EASY, SEE?

04:15.559 --> 04:17.779
YOU NEVER WANT TO DANCE.
-NO, NOT COOL.

04:17.909 --> 04:19.171
NOT NOW.

04:19.302 --> 04:20.476
-COME ON.

04:20.608 --> 04:22.392
MAN.

04:22.523 --> 04:24.394
RANDY, BEER ME, MAN.

04:24.525 --> 04:25.787
-HEY, NO PROBLEM.

04:27.441 --> 04:28.268
-HOW'S IT GOING?
-ALL RIGHT.

04:28.398 --> 04:29.312
-DOING ALL RIGHT?

04:29.443 --> 04:30.748
-HEY, HOBIE'S HERE.

04:31.706 --> 04:32.968
WHAT'S UP, DUDE?

04:41.324 --> 04:43.021
-HEY, HOBIE.
-HEY.

04:43.152 --> 04:44.980
-OH, I'M SO GLAD YOU'RE HERE.

04:45.110 --> 04:46.503
-ME, TOO.

04:46.634 --> 04:47.635
HEY, YOU BETTER TAKE
IT EASY WITH THOSE,

04:47.765 --> 04:49.114
WE'VE GOT TO TRAIN TOMORROW.

04:49.245 --> 04:50.551
-OH, DON'T WORRY,
I ONLY HAD A COUPLE.

04:50.681 --> 04:51.726
-ALL RIGHT.

04:51.856 --> 04:52.944
-I WANT TO BE A
LIFEGUARD TOO MUCH

04:53.075 --> 04:54.511
TO BLOW A SHOT A ROOKIE SCHOOL.

04:54.642 --> 04:56.644
-ALL RIGHT, WELL,
O T W AT 7AM, THEN.

04:56.774 --> 04:57.862
-O T W?

04:57.993 --> 04:59.037
-ON THE WATER.

04:59.168 --> 05:00.952
-OH.

05:01.083 --> 05:02.345
-WE GOT SOME DORY WORK TO DO,
AND SOME PADDLE BOARDING,

05:02.476 --> 05:03.564
BUT I'LL TAKE CARE
OF YOU, DON'T WORRY.

05:03.694 --> 05:05.043
-THANKS, HOBIE.

05:05.174 --> 05:06.828
A SHOT AT BAYWATCH
MEANS EVERYTHING TO ME.

05:10.701 --> 05:12.399
COME ON.
-YEAH.

05:13.878 --> 05:14.879
-HEY, HOBE.

05:15.010 --> 05:16.228
-YEAH, RANDY, WHAT UP?

05:16.359 --> 05:17.099
-WHAT'S UP MAN,
YOU WANT A BREWSKI?

05:17.229 --> 05:18.579
-NO, ACTUALLY, I'M COOL.

05:18.709 --> 05:20.232
HEY, WHEN ARE YOU
SHOVING OFF TO STANFORD?

05:20.363 --> 05:22.060
-IN A MONTH.

05:22.191 --> 05:23.758
COACH HAS GOT ME ENROLLED
IN SOME SUMMER TENNIS CAMP.

05:23.888 --> 05:24.976
HE WANTS TO CHECK THE
TALENT BEFORE CLASSES START.

05:25.107 --> 05:26.500
-YEAH, RIGHT ON.

05:26.630 --> 05:27.631
I'LL SEE YOU ON THE
SPORTS PAGE, RIGHT?

05:27.762 --> 05:30.199
-HEY-HEY, IT'S THE CABANA BOY.

05:30.330 --> 05:31.809
-EASY, DUDES.
-HEY, BE COOL, HUH BRAD.

05:31.940 --> 05:33.942
-I'M JUST SAYING HI
TO AN OLD BUDDY, RIGHT?

05:34.072 --> 05:36.423
LISTEN, YOU GOT ANY
SAND IN THOSE SHORTS,

05:36.553 --> 05:38.163
MR. HERO LIFEGUARD?

05:38.294 --> 05:40.775
-GIVE ME A BREAK, I'VE
NEVER HEARD THAT ONE BEFORE.

05:40.905 --> 05:42.472
AH, HE NUKED ME.

05:42.603 --> 05:45.083
HEY, SO, YOU GONNA GO
TO THE PROM?

05:45.214 --> 05:46.563
-YEAH, I'M GOING WITH LIZ.

05:46.694 --> 05:48.870
YOU'VE ALREADY GRADUATED,
MAN, YOU GOING?

05:51.916 --> 05:53.135
-WAS THINKING ABOUT IT.

05:53.265 --> 05:54.484
-JOSIE AND I ARE.

05:55.137 --> 05:56.747
AIN'T THAT RIGHT, BABY?

05:57.574 --> 05:59.794
COME ON, GUYS, IT'S TIME
FOR THE BOOZE CRUISE.

05:59.924 --> 06:01.099
LET'S GO, COME ON.

06:04.059 --> 06:04.929
ALL ABOARD.

06:06.366 --> 06:07.845
-YOU KNOW WHAT, BRAD?

06:07.976 --> 06:09.369
YOU'VE BEEN DRINKING AND
THESE BOATS HAUL, MAN.

06:09.499 --> 06:10.457
IT'S NOT A GOOD MIX.

06:10.587 --> 06:12.023
-IT'S MY OLD MAN'S BOAT.

06:12.154 --> 06:12.937
IT GOT US HERE,
IT'LL GET US BACK.

06:13.068 --> 06:14.548
-YEAH, WELL, MAYBE,

06:14.678 --> 06:16.114
BUT YOU'RE LOOKING
THROUGH BEER GOGGLES, MAN.

06:16.245 --> 06:17.246
I'VE BEEN DRIVING A
BOAT AT WORK ALL DAY.

06:17.377 --> 06:18.726
-LOOK, WE'RE GOING.

06:18.856 --> 06:20.380
IT'S IN STONE, MAN,
IT'S A DONE DEAL.

06:20.510 --> 06:21.946
-YEAH, ALL RIGHT.

06:22.077 --> 06:23.078
WELL THEN LET ME BE
THE DESIGNATED DRIVER,

06:23.208 --> 06:24.384
GIVE ME THE KEYS.

06:24.514 --> 06:26.255
-BUCHANAN, I KICKED
YOUR BUTT AT SURFING.

06:26.386 --> 06:27.561
I KICKED YOUR BUTT AT HOOPS.

06:27.691 --> 06:29.476
AND I CAN KICK YOUR
BUTT DRIVING A BOAT.

06:29.606 --> 06:30.999
-I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE THINKING, MAN,

06:31.129 --> 06:32.783
BUT YOU NEED TO GIVE
ME THE KEYS, ALL RIGHT?

06:32.914 --> 06:34.132
HEY, TELL HIM.

06:34.263 --> 06:35.351
-JUST LET HOBIE DRIVE.

06:35.482 --> 06:36.657
-YEAH, BRAD, LET HIM DRIVE.

06:36.787 --> 06:38.746
-GIRL: COME ON.
-BOY: YEAH, LET HIM DRIVE.

06:38.876 --> 06:39.921
-GIRL: LET'S GO.

06:40.051 --> 06:41.313
-YOU WANT THESE?
-SMART MOVE.

06:42.271 --> 06:43.446
NOT FUNNY.

06:54.326 --> 06:56.372
[APRIL GRUNTING]

07:01.725 --> 07:02.813
-HEY.

07:02.944 --> 07:04.380
-HI, ROSEMARY.

07:07.514 --> 07:08.384
HEY.

07:10.081 --> 07:11.256
-HEY.

07:11.779 --> 07:13.171
JUST GETTING RID
OF SOME AGGRESSION.

07:14.042 --> 07:15.522
WHAT'S UP?

07:15.652 --> 07:17.698
-UM, DO YOU MIND IF
I ASK YOU A QUESTION?

07:17.828 --> 07:20.048
I KNOW THERE'S SORT OF
AN UNWRITTEN RULE ABOUT

07:20.178 --> 07:22.964
LIFEGUARDS DISCUSSING, UM...

07:25.706 --> 07:27.447
NEVER MIND, IT'S PROBABLY
NONE OF MY BUSINESS.

07:28.970 --> 07:31.668
-IT'S OK, I CAN
TALK ABOUT IT NOW.

07:32.539 --> 07:33.757
-YEAH?
-YEAH.

07:34.628 --> 07:37.718
I HAD A BOUT OF POST
TRAUMATIC STRESS SYNDROME.

07:38.632 --> 07:39.937
-WHAT CAUSES THAT?

07:40.068 --> 07:44.551
-WELL, I TRIED TO
RESCUE THIS MAN,

07:44.681 --> 07:47.728
HIS NAME WAS VIC, AND
I COULDN'T SAVE HIM.

07:47.858 --> 07:49.077
HE DROWNED.

07:49.904 --> 07:51.166
-WOW.

07:51.296 --> 07:52.602
HOW DOES...

07:52.733 --> 07:54.517
I'M SORRY, I'M PROBABLY
WAY OUT OF LINE.

07:54.648 --> 07:56.650
-NO, DON'T WORRY, I'M OK NOW.

07:56.780 --> 07:58.956
I MEAN, AT FIRST
I HAD NIGHTMARES,

07:59.087 --> 08:02.351
AND I KEPT RELIVING IT
OVER AND OVER BUT...

08:04.222 --> 08:06.094
-WHAT DID YOU FEEL?

08:06.224 --> 08:07.791
-GUILT.

08:07.922 --> 08:11.273
I FELT THAT A MAN HAD DIED
BECAUSE OF MY MISTAKE.

08:11.403 --> 08:14.537
AND I WAS BLAMING MYSELF FOR
SOMETHING I SHOULDN'T HAVE.

08:15.233 --> 08:17.018
I GOT SO AFRAID THAT IT
WAS GOING TO HAPPEN AGAIN

08:17.148 --> 08:19.499
THAT I DIDN'T WANT TO
GO BACK TO THAT TOWER.

08:20.630 --> 08:21.544
-WHAT IF...

08:21.675 --> 08:22.719
WHAT IF IT HAPPENS AGAIN?

08:22.850 --> 08:24.678
-WELL, I HOPE IT DOESN'T.

08:24.808 --> 08:26.462
-BUT WHAT IF IT DOES?

08:26.593 --> 08:30.727
-JESSIE, SOMETIMES I
LOOK OUT AT MY WATER AND

08:30.858 --> 08:32.816
THERE ARE A THOUSAND OR
2,000 PEOPLE OUT THERE.

08:32.947 --> 08:35.732
AND UNLESS THEY'RE WAVING
THEIR ARMS OR YELLING FOR HELP,

08:35.863 --> 08:39.388
ONE COULD SLIP UNDER AND
I WOULD NEVER EVEN KNOW.

08:39.519 --> 08:41.520
ALL YOU CAN DO IS TRY YOUR BEST.

08:43.697 --> 08:46.438
[POIGNANT MUSIC]

08:46.569 --> 08:50.530
[BOAT ENGINE REVVING]
[KIDS WHOOPING AND CHEERING]

08:56.971 --> 08:59.060
-RANDY: GO FASTER, HOBIE!

08:59.190 --> 09:01.062
-YOU'RE THE BEST.

09:03.455 --> 09:05.545
[KIDS CHEERING]
[ROWDY MUSIC]

09:08.112 --> 09:10.332
YEAH.

09:38.708 --> 09:39.666
-WHOA.

09:39.796 --> 09:41.450
JOSIE, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

09:44.409 --> 09:47.499
[KIDS SCREAMING]

10:03.951 --> 10:05.953
[WATER LAPPING]

10:06.083 --> 10:09.434
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

10:10.044 --> 10:11.611
-JOSIE!

10:32.066 --> 10:33.241
ALL RIGHT, YOU'RE ALL RIGHT.

10:33.371 --> 10:34.372
[BRAD SPUTTERING]

10:34.503 --> 10:36.984
NOW HOLD ON, HOLD ON RIGHT HERE.

10:39.595 --> 10:42.598
[COUGHING]

10:44.731 --> 10:48.473
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

10:49.953 --> 10:52.216
-RADIO: BAYWATCH
HEADQUARTERS TO SCARAB ONE.

10:52.347 --> 10:54.218
A PRIVATE AIRCRAFT
JUST RADIO'D MAYDAY,

10:54.349 --> 10:56.481
A BOAT HAS FLIPPED DUE
WEST OF THE MARINA.

10:56.612 --> 10:58.440
THE PILOT REPORTS
PASSENGERS IN THE WATER.

10:58.570 --> 11:00.964
PLEASE RESPOND CODE R.

11:07.231 --> 11:10.626
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

11:15.849 --> 11:16.632
-YOU HURT?

11:16.763 --> 11:17.677
-OH, MY LEG.

11:17.807 --> 11:19.417
-YOU'RE GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

11:23.987 --> 11:25.423
-JESSIE, TAKE THE WHEEL.

11:25.554 --> 11:26.337
-OK.

11:26.468 --> 11:28.165
-HOLD ON RIGHT HERE.

11:30.515 --> 11:31.908
-HOBIE, ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

11:32.039 --> 11:34.868
-YEAH, I'M ALL RIGHT, BUT
WE GOT MORE PEOPLE UNDER.

11:38.828 --> 11:41.265
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

11:53.364 --> 11:54.496
-YOU GUYS OK?

11:54.626 --> 11:56.193
[BOYS ANSWER UNINTELLIGIBLY]

11:56.324 --> 11:58.805
HERE, HERE, TAKE THIS,
TAKE A HOLD OF THIS CAN.

12:00.807 --> 12:02.243
GOT IT?

12:05.246 --> 12:08.728
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

12:26.789 --> 12:28.182
-COME ON.

12:28.878 --> 12:29.661
YOU OK?

12:29.792 --> 12:30.750
-YEAH.

12:30.880 --> 12:32.099
-COME ON.

12:35.537 --> 12:36.451
ARE YOU GUYS ALL RIGHT?

12:36.581 --> 12:41.543
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

12:55.078 --> 12:58.212
[SIREN]

13:02.390 --> 13:07.047
[CROWD CHATTER]

13:24.586 --> 13:26.196
-OH GOD.

13:26.327 --> 13:28.851
MY OLD MAN'S BOAT, MAN, HE'S
GOING TO KILL ME AFTER THIS.

13:28.982 --> 13:30.810
-ARE YOU OK, BUCHANAN?

13:30.940 --> 13:32.463
-YEAH, I'M ALL RIGHT.

13:33.464 --> 13:35.902
-BEEN UH, BEEN DRINKING
A LITTLE BEER, HUH?

13:36.032 --> 13:37.251
-NO, I HAVEN'T BEEN DRINKING.

13:37.381 --> 13:38.643
-I CAN SMELL IT.

13:38.774 --> 13:39.949
-WELL, SOME GOT
SPILLED ON ME EARLIER.

13:40.080 --> 13:41.908
I WASN'T DRINKING, I SWEAR.

13:42.038 --> 13:43.561
-I UNDERSTAND IT WAS
YOUR FATHER'S BOAT.

13:43.692 --> 13:44.562
WERE YOU DRIVING?

13:44.693 --> 13:46.129
-I WAS.

13:46.260 --> 13:47.565
-SO WHAT HAPPENED OUT
THERE, HOW DID IT FLIP?

13:51.221 --> 13:52.657
-I DON'T KNOW.

13:53.484 --> 13:55.835
I GUESS I WAS DRIVING TOO FAST,

13:57.010 --> 13:58.750
AND WE HIT A WAKE,

13:59.969 --> 14:01.666
AND I LOST IT.

14:03.494 --> 14:05.018
-I'M GOING TO TAKE
YOU DOWN TO THE STATION

14:05.148 --> 14:06.541
FOR A BLOOD ALCOHOL TEST.
WHY DON'T YOU STAND UP.

14:06.671 --> 14:09.152
-WHAT, HANDCUFFS?

14:09.283 --> 14:10.632
COME ON.

14:10.762 --> 14:12.025
-IT'S PROCEDURE.
-WHAT?

14:12.155 --> 14:13.548
I WASN'T DRINKING, I SWEAR.

14:13.678 --> 14:15.245
BRAD, TELL HIM.

14:15.376 --> 14:17.117
-WE'LL LET THE
TEST DECIDE THAT.

14:20.468 --> 14:22.122
-HOLD ON, ALL
RIGHT, SHE'S HURT.

14:22.252 --> 14:23.775
-JUST LET ME TALK TO HER.
-HOBIE, COME ON, LET'S GO.

14:23.906 --> 14:25.473
-COME ON.

14:25.603 --> 14:27.257
BRAD, TELL HIM.

14:27.388 --> 14:29.651
HEY, I RESCUED THEM ALL.

14:47.364 --> 14:50.628
[ENGINE TURNS OVER]

15:02.684 --> 15:04.338
-OFFICER: RIGHT HERE.

15:12.999 --> 15:14.043
[DOOR CLOSES]

15:17.917 --> 15:19.048
-ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

15:19.831 --> 15:20.920
-YEAH.

15:21.659 --> 15:23.487
I'M REALLY SORRY, DAD.

15:28.928 --> 15:29.885
-WERE YOU DRINKING?

15:30.016 --> 15:31.191
-NO.

15:31.321 --> 15:32.279
I SWEAR.

15:33.280 --> 15:36.587
EVERYBODY ELSE WAS,
THAT'S WHY I WAS DRIVING.

15:36.718 --> 15:38.502
I THOUGHT IT WAS THE
BEST THING TO DO.

15:38.633 --> 15:40.069
-WHY DIDN'T YOU JUST
TAKE THE DAMN KEYS?

15:40.200 --> 15:41.897
-THEY WANTED TO GO.

15:42.680 --> 15:44.900
WE WERE ALL JUST
HAVING A GOOD TIME.

15:46.075 --> 15:48.686
I'VE BEEN DRIVING THE
SCARAB SO GOOD AT WORK,

15:48.817 --> 15:49.600
I WANTED TO SHOW JOSIE.

15:49.731 --> 15:51.124
-THE POLICE REPORT SAID

15:51.254 --> 15:52.342
THERE WERE SIX PEOPLE
ON THE SPEEDBOAT.

15:52.473 --> 15:53.387
YOU KNOW BETTER THAN THAT.

15:53.517 --> 15:56.085
-I KNOW, I HAD
IT UNDER CONTROL.

15:56.781 --> 15:58.348
UNTIL JOSIE WANTED TO GO FASTER.

15:58.479 --> 16:00.698
-OH, GOD, DON'T TELL
ME THIS WHOLE THING

16:00.829 --> 16:02.352
IS ABOUT SHOWING OFF FOR A GIRL!

16:02.483 --> 16:03.701
-NO, I HAD IT.

16:05.181 --> 16:07.836
AND THEN JOSIE PUSHED
DOWN THE THROTTLE.

16:08.489 --> 16:09.838
IT TOOK ABOUT A SECOND.

16:09.969 --> 16:11.883
WE HIT A WAKE OFF
CENTER AND FLIPPED.

16:15.235 --> 16:16.584
-SHE PUSHED THE THROTTLE?

16:16.714 --> 16:18.020
-YES.

16:19.674 --> 16:21.197
-WHY DIDN'T YOU
TELL THE POLICE?

16:21.328 --> 16:22.851
-SHE WANTS TO BE A LIFEGUARD.

16:22.982 --> 16:24.331
WE WERE SUPPOSED TO
TRAIN THIS SUMMER.

16:24.461 --> 16:25.723
-SO YOU COVERED FOR HER.

16:25.854 --> 16:27.595
-BAYWATCH WOULD HAVE NEVER
LET HER BE A LIFEGUARD.

16:27.725 --> 16:28.988
-OH, THIS IS TERRIFIC.

16:29.118 --> 16:30.467
YOU COVER FOR HER,

16:30.598 --> 16:32.165
NOW YOU'RE IN JAIL
BEING HELD RESPONSIBLE.

16:32.861 --> 16:33.818
-SHE'LL TELL YOU SHE DID IT.

16:33.949 --> 16:34.950
-NO, SHE WON'T.

16:35.907 --> 16:38.258
HOBIE, SHE'S IN THE
HOSPITAL, UNCONSCIOUS.

16:42.175 --> 16:44.003
STUPID THING TO DO, STUPID!

16:44.133 --> 16:45.961
-STUPID!
-I KNOW, ALL RIGHT?

16:46.092 --> 16:47.528
I SCREWED UP.

16:47.658 --> 16:49.138
I'M SORRY.

16:49.269 --> 16:50.270
IT HAPPENED.

16:50.400 --> 16:52.533
I WISH IT DIDN'T, BUT IT DID.

16:56.711 --> 16:59.018
IT'S A BIG NIGHTMARE.

16:59.975 --> 17:01.411
-OH, IT'S NO NIGHTMARE.

17:04.196 --> 17:05.111
IT'S REAL.

17:14.903 --> 17:15.730
-APRIL: HEY.

17:15.859 --> 17:17.036
-HI.

17:20.387 --> 17:21.953
APRIL WENT TO AN ATTORNEY.

17:22.737 --> 17:24.173
-AH, THANKS.

17:24.955 --> 17:27.655
-WELL, I GOT SOME
NEWS AND IT'S NOT GOOD.

17:28.786 --> 17:30.875
THE BLOOD TEST RESULTS WON'T
BE READY 'TIL TOMORROW.

17:31.006 --> 17:32.225
-TOMORROW?

17:32.355 --> 17:35.706
-AND THE BAIL HAS
BEEN SET FOR $300,000.

17:35.837 --> 17:37.056
-$300,000.

17:38.883 --> 17:41.016
I CAN'T MAKE THAT BAIL,
THAT'S JUST SO HIGH.

17:42.583 --> 17:44.411
-I CHECKED WITH
THE HOSPITAL AND

17:44.541 --> 17:45.760
THERE WERE SOME BROKEN BONES AND

17:45.890 --> 17:48.415
SOME BAD CUTS BUT THEY
WERE ALL ABLE TO GO HOME.

17:48.545 --> 17:49.677
-SO HOW'S JOSIE?

17:50.634 --> 17:51.722
-SHE'S STILL THERE.

17:52.419 --> 17:53.942
SHE'S IN A COMA.

17:55.248 --> 17:56.597
-OH MY GOD.

18:01.428 --> 18:03.604
-ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

18:06.041 --> 18:07.303
WHAT ARE WE LOOKING AT?

18:07.869 --> 18:08.739
THE TRUTH.

18:09.958 --> 18:11.438
-THE ATTORNEY SAYS THAT IF...

18:12.308 --> 18:13.788
IF JOSIE'S CONDITION...

18:15.268 --> 18:18.749
IF SHE DIES, HOBIE COULD
FACE INVOLUNTARY MANSLAUGHTER

18:18.880 --> 18:21.622
AND, IF CONVICTED,
HE COULD GO TO PRISON.

18:24.538 --> 18:25.495
[DOOR OPENS]

18:27.454 --> 18:28.977
-OH, DAD.

18:29.108 --> 18:30.283
-OFFICER: ALL RIGHT, SON,
WE GOT TO GO.

18:30.935 --> 18:32.328
-I'M SCARED.

18:32.459 --> 18:33.764
-YEAH, I KNOW, ME TOO.

18:33.895 --> 18:35.462
LOOK, I'LL GET YOU
OUT OF HERE, OK?

18:35.592 --> 18:36.680
I'LL GET YOU OUT.

18:40.945 --> 18:44.862
[SOLEMN MUSIC]

19:56.195 --> 19:58.066
-POOR HOBIE, HE
LOOKS SO SCARED.

19:58.197 --> 20:00.068
-YEAH, WELL, HE'S
GOT A REASON TO BE.

20:02.113 --> 20:02.984
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

20:03.637 --> 20:05.073
-HEY.

20:05.204 --> 20:06.770
I'M JUST DOING SOME
REPAIRS ON THE SURF SKI,

20:06.901 --> 20:08.424
THERE'S SOME PRETTY BAD DINGS.

20:08.555 --> 20:09.686
-THOUGHT CHERYL WAS
SUPPOSED TO BE DOING THAT.

20:09.817 --> 20:11.340
-OH, SHE WAS, BUT WE T X'D,

20:11.471 --> 20:13.081
SHE'S WATCHING MY TOWER
AND I'M DOING THE REPAIRS.

20:13.212 --> 20:15.170
-I GIVE OUT THE TOWER
ASSIGNMENTS HERE,

20:15.301 --> 20:16.998
YOU'RE IN TOWER 12, NOT CHERYL.

20:17.128 --> 20:19.261
-I KNOW, BUT SHE REALLY
WANTED TO WATCH THE WATER TODAY

20:19.392 --> 20:21.089
SO I THOUGHT I COULD JUST--
-DON'T.

20:21.220 --> 20:22.656
SHE TWEAKED HER ANKLE
PLAYING RACQUETBALL,

20:22.786 --> 20:24.005
I DON'T WANT HER
IN A TOWER TODAY.

20:25.659 --> 20:26.790
-I'LL TAKE HER TOWER.

20:26.921 --> 20:28.270
-AND I'LL TAKE THE SWITCHBOARD.

20:28.401 --> 20:29.619
-WHAT IS WITH ALL
THIS WHINING STUFF?

20:29.750 --> 20:30.794
YOU'RE ON THE BOARD,
YOU'RE IN 12,

20:30.925 --> 20:32.492
CHERYL'S ON THE SURF SKI.

20:34.624 --> 20:35.451
THE WAY IT IS.

20:36.800 --> 20:41.631
[MELLOW MUSIC]

20:49.596 --> 20:50.379
-HEY.

20:50.510 --> 20:52.251
-HEY.

20:52.381 --> 20:54.601
-YOU'RE PRETTY LUCKY, I WISH
I COULD WORK A TOWER TODAY.

20:54.731 --> 20:56.429
-MAYBE YOU COULD CONVINCE
MITCH TO LET US TRADE.

20:56.559 --> 20:57.821
-WELL, YOU HEARD HIM.

20:58.996 --> 21:00.563
JESS, ARE YOU OK?

21:02.086 --> 21:03.392
-YEAH, I'M FINE.

21:04.480 --> 21:05.351
WHY?

21:06.047 --> 21:07.614
-YOU SEEM A LITTLE ANTSY.

21:10.138 --> 21:11.182
-I'M OK.

21:13.750 --> 21:15.796
-DID WHAT I SAY UPSET YOU?

21:21.192 --> 21:21.976
-NO.

21:22.106 --> 21:23.325
I MEAN...

21:24.631 --> 21:25.849
IT'S HORRIBLE, WHAT HAPPENED.

21:26.502 --> 21:29.592
-YOU ASKED, "WHAT
IF IT HAPPENS AGAIN?"

21:30.767 --> 21:32.029
AND I DON'T KNOW.

21:32.160 --> 21:34.858
WE'RE LIFEGUARDS
AND WE SAVE LIVES,

21:34.989 --> 21:37.121
AND WE DO THE BEST
THAT WE CAN, BUT,

21:38.209 --> 21:39.689
BOTTOM LINE IS, IT CAN HAPPEN.

21:41.387 --> 21:42.866
-COMES WITH THE
TERRITORY, RIGHT?

21:44.303 --> 21:45.565
I KNOW.

21:46.566 --> 21:48.611
I'M GOING TO GO RELIEVE
CHERYL AT HER TOWER.

21:50.526 --> 21:52.789
-JESS, DO YOU WANT TO
TALK ABOUT THIS AFTER WORK?

21:52.920 --> 21:54.530
-NO, I'M OK.

21:55.488 --> 21:56.619
SEE YOU.

22:01.798 --> 22:03.322
-WHAT ABOUT MY CAR?

22:05.062 --> 22:06.499
YEAH, I KNOW IT'S NOT PAID FOR,

22:06.629 --> 22:07.891
BUT ISN'T THERE SOMETHING--

22:09.719 --> 22:11.895
YEAH, I-I-I-I KNOW,
I KNOW, I KNOW.

22:12.722 --> 22:14.245
ALL RIGHT,
WELL THANK YOU ANYWAY.

22:14.376 --> 22:15.508
[PHONE SLAMS] DAMN IT.

22:15.638 --> 22:16.726
[KNOCKING]

22:16.857 --> 22:17.901
YEAH, COME IN.

22:25.213 --> 22:26.083
WHAT'S THIS?

22:27.215 --> 22:28.434
-IT'S JUST RAINY-DAY MONEY,

22:30.653 --> 22:31.828
AND IT'S RAINING.

22:36.790 --> 22:39.532
RAINY-DAY MONEY, A
CHECK FOR $25,000?

22:39.662 --> 22:41.490
-YOU REMEMBER
THOSE DESIGNS I DID

22:41.621 --> 22:43.623
FOR CALIFORNIA LIFESTYLE SHOES?

22:44.232 --> 22:45.494
IT'S MY FIRST ROYALTY CHECK.

22:46.930 --> 22:48.105
IT'S YOURS.

22:48.976 --> 22:50.151
-THANKS, BUT I CAN'T TAKE THIS.

22:50.281 --> 22:52.371
-HOBIE IS ONE OF US, MITCH.

22:52.936 --> 22:54.155
AND WE TAKE CARE OF OUR OWN.

22:58.028 --> 22:59.116
-IT'S THE DEED TO MY HOUSE.

23:02.032 --> 23:04.121
IT'S JUST NOT ENOUGH COLLATERAL
TO BAIL HIM OUT OF JAIL.

23:05.296 --> 23:06.950
DOESN'T EVEN COME CLOSE.

23:12.478 --> 23:13.653
I'LL NEVER FORGET THIS.

23:16.264 --> 23:17.308
YOU WANT TO COVER FOR ME?

23:18.571 --> 23:20.573
I'M GOING TO GO GET
MY BOY OUT OF JAIL.

23:22.488 --> 23:26.361
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

23:32.411 --> 23:35.326
[MONITOR BEEPING]

23:41.202 --> 23:45.598
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

24:00.134 --> 24:01.440
-HEY BABE.

24:03.006 --> 24:04.834
BROUGHT YOU SOME FLOWERS.

24:10.405 --> 24:12.102
JOSIE, YOU GOT TO WAKE UP.

24:12.973 --> 24:14.931
HEY, YOU GOT A PROM
TO GET READY FOR.

24:16.890 --> 24:19.240
YOU KNOW WE GOTTA TRAIN
FOR ROOKIE SCHOOL.

24:29.990 --> 24:31.818
I'M SO SORRY, JOSIE.

24:51.925 --> 24:52.969
-STILL NO CHANGE?

24:53.492 --> 24:54.580
-SHE'S THE SAME.

24:56.103 --> 24:57.931
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING
NEAR MY DAUGHTER?

24:58.061 --> 24:59.889
-I JUST CAME TO
SEE HOW SHE'S DOING.

25:00.020 --> 25:01.630
-HAVEN'T YOU DONE
ENOUGH ALREADY?

25:01.761 --> 25:03.806
-UH, LOOK, LET'S JUST
CALM DOWN HERE, OK?

25:05.199 --> 25:06.069
I UNDERSTAND HOW YOU FEEL, BUT--

25:06.200 --> 25:07.462
-ARE YOU HIS FATHER?

25:08.071 --> 25:09.377
-YES.

25:09.508 --> 25:11.118
-THEN YOU DON'T
UNDERSTAND HOW I FEEL,

25:11.248 --> 25:13.337
BECAUSE YOUR CHILD IS AWAKE
STANDING RIGHT NEXT TO YOU.

25:13.468 --> 25:15.122
MY CHILD IS ASLEEP,

25:15.252 --> 25:16.819
AND I DON'T KNOW IF SHE'S
EVER GOING TO WAKE UP.

25:16.950 --> 25:20.649
-ALL RIGHT, LOOK, HOBIE
IS NOT COMPLETELY INNOCENT,

25:22.259 --> 25:23.522
BUT JOSIE ISN'T EITHER.

25:25.045 --> 25:26.176
-WHAT THE HELL ARE
YOU TALKING ABOUT?

25:29.223 --> 25:30.877
-LISTEN, I WAS
DRIVING THE BOAT,

25:32.226 --> 25:34.054
BUT JOSIE PUSHED
DOWN THE THROTTLE.

25:34.184 --> 25:36.535
THAT'S WHY WE WERE
GOING SO FAST.

25:36.665 --> 25:38.145
THAT'S WHY WE FLIPPED.

25:43.672 --> 25:45.021
-I DON'T BELIEVE A
WORD YOU'RE SAYING.

25:45.152 --> 25:46.283
-WELL IT'S TRUE.

25:46.414 --> 25:47.284
YOU CAN ASK BRAD.

25:47.415 --> 25:48.503
HE SAW.

25:50.636 --> 25:51.506
TELL HIM.

25:53.247 --> 25:54.640
-IS IT TRUE?

26:00.515 --> 26:01.908
IS IT?

26:03.474 --> 26:05.476
-WE WERE ALL
HAVING A GOOD TIME.

26:08.610 --> 26:10.960
AND THEN THINGS JUST GOT
A LITTLE OUT OF CONTROL.

26:11.091 --> 26:13.484
HOBIE KEPT GOING
FASTER AND FASTER.

26:14.094 --> 26:17.010
WE KEPT BEGGING HIM TO
SLOW DOWN BUT HE WOULDN'T.

26:17.793 --> 26:20.100
IT WAS LIKE HE WAS
TRYING TO IMPRESS JOSIE.

26:20.230 --> 26:21.841
THE BOAT WAS GETTING AIR,

26:21.971 --> 26:23.146
WE WERE BOUNCING
ALL OVER THE PLACE,

26:23.277 --> 26:25.105
I MEAN, I COULD
BARELY HANG ON INSIDE.

26:25.975 --> 26:29.152
I GUESS HE WAS PLAYING
CHICKEN OR SOMETHING.

26:29.805 --> 26:31.024
HE JUST BARELY MISSED
HITTING THE BELL.

26:31.677 --> 26:34.462
JOSIE WAS SO AFRAID
SHE STARTED TO CRY.

26:35.158 --> 26:36.116
-STOP, PLEASE.

26:36.246 --> 26:37.683
-I TRIED TO PULL HIM AWAY.

26:37.813 --> 26:39.815
WE WRESTLED, I ALMOST HAD HIM.

26:40.816 --> 26:41.861
HOBIE JUST LOST IT.

26:41.991 --> 26:43.384
-YOU'RE LYING.

26:43.514 --> 26:44.472
-MITCH: ALL RIGHT.
-HOBIE: YOU'RE A LIAR.

26:44.603 --> 26:46.735
[INDISTINGUISHABLY YELLING]

26:46.866 --> 26:48.345
THAT'S NOT HOW IT HAPPENED.

26:48.476 --> 26:49.869
JOSIE PUSHED THE THROTTLE
DOWN, HE'S LYING.

26:49.999 --> 26:51.131
-YOU DID IT.

26:51.261 --> 26:52.741
YOU WERE MESSING AROUND
AND WE FLIPPED, YOU.

26:52.872 --> 26:54.395
YOU FLIPPED THE BOAT,
YOU DID IT.

26:54.525 --> 26:56.266
[ALL YELLING]

26:56.397 --> 26:58.355
-YOU PUT MY DAUGHTER IN A COMA,

26:58.486 --> 27:00.096
AND THEN YOU LIE ABOUT IT WHEN

27:00.227 --> 27:02.055
SHE'S NOT ABLE TO
DEFEND HERSELF?

27:02.185 --> 27:03.056
YOU DISGUST ME.

27:03.186 --> 27:04.797
-NO, I DIDN'T

27:04.927 --> 27:06.059
-BRAD: HE'S LYING.
-MITCH: NOT HERE, NOT NOW.

27:06.189 --> 27:07.582
-NO, NO, NO, THERE'S
GOING TO BE MORE.

27:07.713 --> 27:08.931
I'M BRINGING A
LAWSUIT AGAINST YOU.

27:09.062 --> 27:09.584
YOU ARE GOING TO PAY
FOR WHAT YOU DID.

27:09.715 --> 27:10.933
BIG TIME!

27:13.806 --> 27:16.069
[SOLEMN MUSIC]

27:23.511 --> 27:24.643
-MORNIN'.

27:25.513 --> 27:26.645
-HEY.

27:28.429 --> 27:29.517
-ROUGH NIGHT?

27:30.649 --> 27:32.172
I HEARD YOU WALKING
AROUND DOWNSTAIRS

27:32.302 --> 27:33.826
UNTIL FOUR O'CLOCK
IN THE MORNING.

27:33.956 --> 27:37.177
-YEAH, I KNOW, I
COULDN'T STOP THINKING.

27:38.613 --> 27:40.876
-ANYWAY, WHICH TOWER
AM I WORKING TODAY?

27:42.312 --> 27:43.662
-HOBIE.

27:47.187 --> 27:49.537
I TALKED TO THE CHIEF THIS
MORNING ABOUT THE SITUATION.

27:50.669 --> 27:53.410
SHE FEELS, 'TIL IT'S RESOLVED,

27:54.629 --> 27:55.978
AT LEAST UNTIL THE ARRAIGNMENT,

27:56.109 --> 27:59.765
THAT, UM, YOU BE PLACED
ON TEMPORARY LEAVE.

28:00.983 --> 28:02.202
-YOU DON'T BELIEVE ME, DO YOU?

28:02.332 --> 28:04.030
-OH, YOU KNOW BETTER THAN
THAT, I'M YOUR FATHER.

28:05.074 --> 28:06.641
BUT I'M ALSO YOUR BOSS,

28:06.772 --> 28:08.164
I GOT TO THINK ABOUT WHAT'S
BEST FOR BAYWATCH HERE.

28:08.861 --> 28:10.732
LOOK, IF IT WAS NEWMIE OR MANNY

28:10.863 --> 28:12.778
OR ANY OTHER LIFEGUARD
IN YOUR POSITION,

28:13.517 --> 28:14.693
I'D HAVE TO DO THE SAME THING.

28:18.305 --> 28:19.654
YOU'RE JUST GOING TO
HAVE TO HANG IN THERE.

28:22.396 --> 28:23.702
I'M SORRY.

28:26.574 --> 28:28.228
-THANKS A LOT.

28:30.970 --> 28:32.058
BOSS.

28:37.411 --> 28:40.631
[ENERGETIC MUSIC]

28:51.077 --> 28:54.254
[VOCALIZING]

29:09.443 --> 29:14.665
♪ I FEEL SO DEEP

29:14.796 --> 29:18.191
♪ BELOW THE SURFACE

29:18.321 --> 29:22.325
♪ NOT EVEN THE SUN

29:22.456 --> 29:27.722
♪ CAN BURN THROUGH THIS DARKNESS

29:27.853 --> 29:32.118
♪ HELP ME IM INSANE AND I KNOW IT

29:32.248 --> 29:36.687
♪ HELP ME IM AFRAID YOU DON'T NOTICE

29:36.818 --> 29:42.389
