-[SOBBING] NO, I CAN'T.

30:37.792 --> 30:39.838
I CAN'T.

30:39.968 --> 30:42.014
[SCREAMS]

30:42.841 --> 30:43.711
-JESSIE.

30:51.501 --> 30:53.025
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

30:53.155 --> 30:54.504
JESS, WHAT'S WRONG?

31:03.296 --> 31:04.340
HOLD ON, WAIT UP.

31:04.471 --> 31:06.603
JESSIE, I AM WORRIED ABOUT YOU.

31:06.734 --> 31:08.214
WHAT WENT ON BACK
THERE IN THE TOWER?

31:08.344 --> 31:09.868
-YOU DON'T HAVE TO
WORRY ANY MORE, APRIL.

31:09.998 --> 31:11.826
-I'M QUITTING.
-WHAT, WHY?

31:11.957 --> 31:14.220
-BECAUSE IF WHAT HAPPENED
TO YOU HAPPENS TO ME...

31:14.350 --> 31:15.482
I JUST DON'T KNOW.

31:15.612 --> 31:17.266
WHAT IF I LET SOMEONE DIE?

31:17.397 --> 31:19.878
-OK, WELL, THINK ABOUT ALL
THE LIVES THAT YOU CAN SAVE.

31:20.008 --> 31:22.054
WHAT IF YOU'RE NOT
OUT THERE TO TRY?

31:22.924 --> 31:24.056
JESSIE, YOU'RE A NATURAL.

31:24.186 --> 31:25.405
YOU HAVE WHAT IT
TAKES TO BE ONE OF

31:25.535 --> 31:27.320
THE BEST LIFEGUARDS AT BAYWATCH.

31:27.450 --> 31:28.843
-I FROZE UP TODAY.

31:28.974 --> 31:30.323
I COMPLETELY FELL APART.

31:31.063 --> 31:32.891
I'M NO GOOD TO YOU, TO BAYWATCH,

31:33.021 --> 31:35.545
ESPECIALLY TO ANYONE OUT THERE.

31:36.416 --> 31:37.896
I CAN'T GO BACK IN
THAT TOWER, APRIL.

31:38.679 --> 31:39.898
I JUST CAN'T.

31:40.637 --> 31:41.551
-LISTEN,

31:42.596 --> 31:44.337
THE COASTIES CALLED
IN A GHOST NET,

31:44.467 --> 31:46.034
AND I HAVE TO GO PICK IT UP.

31:46.165 --> 31:47.949
COME WITH ME.

31:48.080 --> 31:50.865
FINISH YOUR SHIFT, AND THEN,
IF YOU STILL FEEL THE SAME WAY,

31:50.996 --> 31:53.607
THEN YOU CAN DECIDE
WHAT YOU WANT TO DO.

31:55.043 --> 31:56.436
-BLONDE: I'VE HEARD THIS IS

31:56.566 --> 31:58.003
THE BEST SPOT FOR
SNORKELING IN MALIBU.

31:58.133 --> 31:59.178
-BRUNETTE: I SHOULD
HAVE BROUGHT MY CAMERA.

31:59.308 --> 32:00.831
COME ON.

32:11.886 --> 32:16.064
[EASY-GOING MUSIC]

32:34.343 --> 32:37.129
[SCARAB ENGINE RUNNING]

32:51.665 --> 32:54.146
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

33:10.597 --> 33:11.728
-HELP!

33:11.859 --> 33:12.642
-WHAT' THE MATTER?

33:12.773 --> 33:14.427
-MY FRIEND'S DOWN THERE.

33:14.557 --> 33:15.732
SHE'S STUCK IN SOME KIND OF NET,

33:15.863 --> 33:17.082
PLEASE HELP HER.

33:17.212 --> 33:19.171
-GET HER ABOARD
AND THEN HELP ME.

33:24.480 --> 33:30.138
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

33:35.926 --> 33:37.754
-OVER HERE, I'LL HELP YOU UP.

33:41.019 --> 33:44.935
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

33:46.328 --> 33:47.503
-ARE YOU OK?

33:47.634 --> 33:49.940
-I'M FINE, PLEASE
HELP MY FRIEND.

33:53.596 --> 33:54.945
-SHE'S TANGLED
IN THE DRIFT NET,

33:55.076 --> 33:56.164
GET ME A KNIFE.

34:01.256 --> 34:03.171
-JESSIE, GET ME
THE KNIFE, HURRY!

34:21.755 --> 34:22.886
-OH.

34:24.844 --> 34:29.719
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

34:45.126 --> 34:47.085
-JESSIE, GIVE US A HAND.

34:48.085 --> 34:49.130
HELP HER UP.

35:05.059 --> 35:08.802
[WAVES CRASHING]
[CROWD CHATTER]

35:20.335 --> 35:21.858
-YO, BUCHANAN.

35:24.644 --> 35:26.689
LOCALS ONLY, MAN,
NO KOOKS ALLOWED.

35:26.820 --> 35:28.256
GO FIND A BREAK SOMEWHERE ELSE.

35:28.387 --> 35:29.910
-WHATEVER, BRAD, SHUT UP.

35:30.040 --> 35:31.390
-LOOK,YOU WOULDN'T
BE IN SO MUCH TROUBLE

35:31.520 --> 35:33.043
IF YOU HADN'T'VE PUSHED
THAT THROTTLE SO HARD.

35:33.174 --> 35:34.436
-YOU KNOW I DIDN'T
PUSH THAT THROTTLE--

35:34.567 --> 35:35.655
-LOOK, I SAW YOU, MAN.

35:36.264 --> 35:38.092
-YOU'RE A LIAR AND YOU KNOW IT.

35:40.355 --> 35:41.400
-OH YEAH?

35:42.792 --> 35:45.447
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]
[BOYS GRUNTING]

35:49.016 --> 35:51.801
[BLOWS LANDING]
[GRUNTING AND GROANING]

36:01.768 --> 36:03.596
[SIREN]

36:14.433 --> 36:15.347
-BREAK IT UP.

36:15.477 --> 36:16.957
BREAK IT UP!

36:17.087 --> 36:18.872
BREAK IT UP!

36:22.963 --> 36:24.094
KNOCK IT OFF!

36:24.660 --> 36:25.835
KNOCK IT OFF!

36:26.836 --> 36:27.794
KNOCK IT OFF.

36:27.924 --> 36:29.404
COME ON.

36:30.623 --> 36:31.972
-BRAD: HE STARTED IT.

36:32.102 --> 36:33.582
-COME ON, COME ON,
OUT OF THE WATER.

36:33.713 --> 36:35.323
OUT OF THE WATER, COME ON.

36:36.368 --> 36:37.325
COME ON.

36:42.548 --> 36:43.897
-ALL RIGHT.
-THIS ISN'T OVER YET,

36:44.027 --> 36:44.854
CABANA BOY, YOU KNOW THAT.
-THAT'S IT.

36:45.507 --> 36:47.117
KNOCK IT OFF!
OFF THE BEACH.

36:47.248 --> 36:48.684
YOU, TOO, OFF THE BEACH.

36:49.468 --> 36:50.686
WHAT ARE YOU THINKING, HUH?

36:50.817 --> 36:51.992
HUH?

36:52.122 --> 36:53.298
-IT'S NO BIG DEAL.

36:53.428 --> 36:54.995
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
IT'S NO BIG DEAL?

36:55.125 --> 36:56.431
YOU ALREADY MADE
ONE HUGE MISTAKE.

36:56.562 --> 36:57.867
YOU DODGED THAT BULLET.

36:57.998 --> 36:59.565
YOU PUNCH THIS GUYS
LIGHTS OUT, MAN,

36:59.695 --> 37:00.522
YOU LOSE YOUR JOB.

37:01.393 --> 37:02.742
-HE STARTED IT.
-OH, HE STARTED.

37:02.872 --> 37:03.830
WHAT ARE YOU, SOME LITTLE KID?

37:03.960 --> 37:05.701
WHEN ARE YOU GOING
TO GROW UP, HUH?

37:07.312 --> 37:11.751
HOBIE, I PUT OUR HOUSE
UP TO BAIL YOU OUT.

37:11.881 --> 37:15.842
APRIL GAVE ME A CHECK
FOR $25,000 TO HELP.

37:16.712 --> 37:18.975
NOW, YOU GOT A LOT OF PEOPLE
BELIEVING IN YOU, MAN.

37:19.889 --> 37:21.282
YOU CAN'T LET US DOWN.

37:24.154 --> 37:24.938
ALL RIGHT?

37:25.068 --> 37:26.374
-YEAH.
ALL RIGHT.

37:27.157 --> 37:28.246
HOSPITAL CALLED.

37:28.985 --> 37:29.856
-JOSIE?

37:30.857 --> 37:32.119
-YEAH.
-LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.

37:32.250 --> 37:36.515
[SOLEMN MUSIC]

37:50.833 --> 37:51.704
-HOBIE.

37:55.142 --> 37:56.099
-I DON'T WANT YOU HERE.

37:57.710 --> 37:59.189
-HE'S MY FRIEND, DADDY.

37:59.320 --> 38:00.887
-FRIEND?

38:01.017 --> 38:02.758
IF IT WEREN'T FOR HIM YOU
WOULDN'T BE IN THIS HOSPITAL.

38:02.889 --> 38:04.064
-THAT'S NOT TRUE.

38:06.109 --> 38:09.025
-WHY DON'T YOU JUST
STAY A WHILE, BRAD.

38:10.026 --> 38:12.594
-JOSIE, BRAD SAID THAT I
PUSHED THE THROTTLE DOWN.

38:12.725 --> 38:13.552
-WHAT?

38:13.682 --> 38:16.163
BRAD, WHY WOULD YOU SAY THAT?

38:16.294 --> 38:17.425
DIDN'T YOU TELL HIM?

38:19.384 --> 38:20.950
-YEAH, BUT HE
DOESN'T BELIEVE ME.

38:21.516 --> 38:22.909
MAYBE HE'LL BELIEVE YOU.

38:23.997 --> 38:25.085
-DADDY.

38:26.826 --> 38:28.306
I PUSHED THE THROTTLE DOWN.

38:30.351 --> 38:32.397
WE GOT GOING TOO FAST.

38:33.398 --> 38:34.964
IT WASN'T HOBIE'S FAULT.

38:35.791 --> 38:37.097
IT WAS MINE.

38:38.185 --> 38:39.055
ME.

38:39.708 --> 38:40.579
-BUT...

38:40.709 --> 38:42.232
BRAD SAID THAT HOBIE...

38:44.713 --> 38:46.585
-YOU CAN GO NOW, BRAD.

38:49.588 --> 38:50.632
-UH.

38:52.242 --> 38:55.071
I AM SO SORRY, I...

38:56.290 --> 38:58.031
I OWE YOU BOTH A BIG APOLOGY.

39:00.207 --> 39:01.077
-IT'S ALL GOOD.

39:05.734 --> 39:09.912
[TENDER MUSIC]

39:22.925 --> 39:25.624
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

39:28.496 --> 39:29.932
-WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

39:32.979 --> 39:34.110
-I'M QUITTING.

39:34.981 --> 39:36.112
-NO YOU'RE NOT.

39:37.679 --> 39:39.246
YOU HAVEN'T EVEN STARTED.

39:39.986 --> 39:41.596
-SOMEONE COULD HAVE
DROWNED OUT THERE TODAY,

39:41.727 --> 39:42.510
BECAUSE OF ME.

39:42.641 --> 39:44.425
-TOMORROW'S A DIFFERENT STORY.

39:45.121 --> 39:46.993
JESSIE, YOU'RE YOUNG.

39:47.776 --> 39:48.603
YOU'LL GROW.

39:49.648 --> 39:51.476
LOOK, YOU ALREADY HAVE
MORE NATURAL TALENT THAN

39:51.606 --> 39:53.129
JUST ABOUT ANY LIFEGUARD
I'VE EVER SEEN.

39:54.479 --> 39:55.349
HEY.

39:55.915 --> 39:57.220
YOU'RE GOOD.

39:58.178 --> 39:59.048
WE NEED YOU.

40:01.268 --> 40:02.574
-LET ME THINK IT OVER AND

40:02.704 --> 40:03.575
I'LL TALK TO YOU
ABOUT IT LATER, OK?

40:03.705 --> 40:04.924
-YEAH, WHEN?

40:07.361 --> 40:08.971
-TOMORROW, 6:30.

40:10.756 --> 40:13.106
-TOMORROW, 6:30.

40:23.029 --> 40:24.378
TALKED TO JESSIE,

40:24.509 --> 40:26.249
SHE'LL BE HERE TOMORROW
MORNING AT 06:30.

40:26.380 --> 40:27.555
I THINK THINGS ARE
GOING TO WORK OUT.

40:27.686 --> 40:29.122
-OH, GOOD, I WAS
WORRIED ABOUT HER.

40:30.863 --> 40:32.212
-HEY GUYS.
-HEY!

40:32.342 --> 40:33.909
-HAD A GREAT SHIFT.

40:34.040 --> 40:34.997
IT'S GOOD TO BE BACK ON THE JOB.

40:35.128 --> 40:36.477
-WELL, IT'S GOOD
TO HAVE YOU BACK.

40:36.608 --> 40:38.566
-I WANTED TO THANK
YOU GUYS, ACTUALLY,

40:38.697 --> 40:40.960
FOR STANDING BY ME
AND BELIEVING IN ME.

40:41.090 --> 40:42.962
-WELL, IT'S THE EASIEST
THING IN THE WORLD TO DO.

40:43.092 --> 40:44.354
-I THINK YOU LEARNED
SOMETHING, HUH?

40:44.485 --> 40:45.704
-DEFINITELY.

40:47.575 --> 40:49.011
-ALL RIGHT, WELL, UH...

40:49.664 --> 40:50.491
GO ON.

40:51.318 --> 40:52.101
-GO WHERE?

40:52.232 --> 40:53.233
-THERE.

40:57.498 --> 40:59.282
-WHOO, I'LL SEE YOU GUYS LATER.

41:01.763 --> 41:03.112
WHAT'S UP, BABY?

41:03.243 --> 41:04.200
-HI.

41:04.331 --> 41:06.246
[ROMANTIC MUSIC]

41:10.163 --> 41:12.992
-ISN'T KISSING A GIRL ON
DUTY AGAINST REGULATIONS?

41:13.122 --> 41:14.733
-I DON'T THINK THAT'S KISSING,

41:14.863 --> 41:16.386
I THINK THAT'S
KIND OF LIKE, UH...

41:16.517 --> 41:18.650
SHORT OF BREATH, UM...

41:18.780 --> 41:22.088
HE'S DOING WHAT EVERY
RED-BLOODED AMERICAN LIFEGUARD

41:22.218 --> 41:24.046
SHOULD DO IN HIS SITUATION.

41:25.918 --> 41:27.746
-SHE'S A LITTLE OUT
OF SHAPE, ISN'T SHE?

41:27.876 --> 41:30.226
-YEAH, YEAH. [APRIL LAUGHS]

41:31.053 --> 41:32.272
COME ON, COME ON.

41:32.402 --> 41:34.361
[APRIL GIGGLING]

41:44.240 --> 41:47.156
-♪ [END THEME PLAYING]
